b'$SV Put another way (updated for current prices); buy a warrant on its own right now, $1.77. Buy a unit ($SVSVU), short a share ($SV), and get that same warrant for 52 cents. #strategery https://t.co/aPK2cbi5Y0'

b'So if you like Spring Valley Acq (sustainability, yeah!); a share $SV costs $10.45. A warrant $SVSVW costs $1.75. A unit $SVSVU (a share and half a warrant) costs $10.75. Tight spreads and liquid, not an isolated thing. #YouDoTheMath #SPACArb'

b'Trimmed 10% of my $DM position around 21 to fund more clean energy plays. Took some $SV @ 10.09 & $DCRB @ 10.66'
b'@SpacVet $DCRB is another one, not quite as cheap as $SV and $SPRQ.U, perhaps not quite as sexy as $ACTC. Maybe it is the porridge that is just right? https://t.co/LjNqKkAVXW'

b'Deals will get overlooked, don\'t forget the "older" ones. A couple of sustainability SPACs can still be had for barely over NAV; I like $ACTC but it has been running (unit is mid $12\'s). Meanwhile, units of $SPRQ and $SV are in the $10\'s for a unit (all three have HALF warrant).'
